# CleanSlate Pro — Cursor AI Rules

## Project overview
End-of-tenancy cleaning automation platform. Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind.
AI agent runs via NemoClaw (local sandbox) connecting to Nemotron 3 Super via NVIDIA cloud.

## Architecture
- `app/` — Next.js pages and API routes (App Router)
- `lib/agent.ts` — All NemoClaw/OpenClaw communication lives here
- `lib/store.ts` — In-memory data store (replace with Prisma for production)
- `lib/email.ts` — Nodemailer email sending

## Key rules when editing
1. All AI agent calls go through `lib/agent.ts` — never call NemoClaw directly from pages
2. The agent always has a fallback (rule-based) path so the app works without NemoClaw running
3. Use `'use client'` only when needed (forms, state, interactivity)
4. All API routes are in `app/api/*/route.ts`
5. Brand colour is `brand-600` (#16a34a green) — use Tailwind `brand-*` classes

## NemoClaw connection
- Local URL: `http://localhost:3284` (set in .env.local as NEMOCLAW_API_URL)  
- Session ID: `tenancy-agent`
- The agent runs Nemotron 3 Super via NVIDIA cloud through the NemoClaw privacy proxy
- If NemoClaw isn't running, `askAgent()` returns `'__FALLBACK__'` and rule-based logic kicks in

## Adding new features
- New pages: add to `app/[page-name]/page.tsx`
- New API endpoints: add to `app/api/[endpoint]/route.ts`
- New agent tasks: add a function to `lib/agent.ts` following the pattern of `generateQuote()`

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only — no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Brand green: `brand-600` for buttons, `brand-50/100` for backgrounds
- Consistent border radius: `rounded-xl` for cards, `rounded-lg` for inputs
- Status badges use the CSS classes in `globals.css` (status-new, status-booked, etc.)

## When adding a database (production)
Replace `lib/store.ts` with Prisma:
```bash
npm install prisma @prisma/client
npx prisma init --datasource-provider sqlite
```
Then update all imports from `@/lib/store` to use Prisma client.
